key_insights: Don't trade FOMC mornings - options premiums are expensive, market chops around, statistically you will lose 10x more than you make over time
Use Fibonacci retracement (0.55 level) when you don't have predetermined price levels to trade off
One third of S&P 500 weighted index is due to the Mag Seven stocks (Microsoft, Alphabet, Meta, Amazon, etc.)
Opening Range Breakout (ORB) can provide excellent entry signals when aligned with other technical levels
Don't fight the trend - wait for pullbacks to key levels rather than shorting strength
Be patient - don't buy into sellers, wait for price to come to demand zones
Watch for liquidity grabs and how price moves from liquidity level to liquidity level
Earnings will be more important than FOMC for market direction this week - focus on capital spend guidance for AI infrastructure

Big tech earnings week: Meta, Microsoft, Alphabet (Wed), Amazon, Apple, Coinbase (Thu)

summary: Bill Fanter provides a comprehensive market outlook for the week of October 27th, focusing on FOMC rate decision and major tech earnings (Meta, Microsoft, Alphabet, Amazon, Apple). He emphasizes not trading FOMC mornings due to poor statistical outcomes, and demonstrates multiple technical analysis techniques including Fibonacci retracements, opening range breakouts, gap fills, and liquidity levels. Key focus is on Mag Seven stocks which comprise one-third of S&P 500 weighting, with specific entry zones identified for each major tech stock.
